replies.text:
@kerry62  A warm welcome to the Hope course, please forgive me if this is a duplicate reply. Technology is not my friend lol. 

There are lots of straegies within the hope course that can help with daily struggles. It's also a safe place to network with other sufferers who can share their experiences and what has helped them during their IIH journey. 

I am looking forward to engaging with you as we progress through the Hope programme.

@ellie18 Your feelings are valid and I am certain many others have similar experiences, I certainly did  for a long time after diagnosis. The IIH UK website is a good source of information. I will ensure the link is posted as sadly I am currently unable to add a link here.

The hope programe is tailored for people experiencing the chalenges IIH poses, you will find information here, and people who understand. 

I hope you find the programme helpful and I am looking forward to completing the programme with you 😊

@amy79 I am certain many others here can relate; I certainly can. It is natural to have difficulties accepting one condition; with more, it's even harder. I really do emphasise having several conditions myself. 

Be kind to yourself, you are going through some big adjustments, your feelings and actions are so very valid. 

I hope some of the strategies in the Hope programme resonate with you and are helpful. Please know you are not alone.
